                <h1>Discovering Andy Warhol: The Icon of Pop Art</h1>
                <p>Andy Warhol, born Andrew Warhola in 1928, was an influential American artist known for his role in the pop art movement. He merged fine art with commercial techniques, famously featuring celebrities and everyday consumer products. Warhol's innovative methods, including silkscreen printing, reshaped contemporary art. He died in 1987, leaving a lasting legacy.</p>
